{"_id":"ApIaXAN5MsIKHoV9","name":"The Three Fates Spellburn Actions","permission":{"default":0,"wWErSsSXezizF0nw":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"RollTable.apW7Tw7rPDGCtI3p"}},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/triple-skulls.svg","description":"While the universe can seem cold and uncaring, agents of the Fates understand that it is simply resolving toward a preordained destiny and that too much chaos threatens to tear the skein of creation. Thus spellburning in the name of\nthe Three Fates most often manifests as an orderly rite, the caster petitioning the Fates for inner wisdom on the workings of the spheres. This, in turn, grants the caster’s spells extra potency. When a caster utilizes spellburn, roll [[/roll 1d4]] and consult the table below or build off the suggestions to create an event specific to your home campaign.","results":[{"_id":"CxhT6Q3kzY7qNJyC","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Apprehending the majesty of his role in the ordered universe exhausts the caster (expressed as Stamina, Strength, or Agility loss). The caster must succeed on a DC 15 Will save or lose all benefits of the spellburn. If the caster succeeds on the save, his hard-won wisdom grants him a +1 bonus to all future attempts at the spell. (Such a bonus can only be gained once per spell.)","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[1,1],"drawn":false},{"_id":"QUavTIpNRcYmSCEr","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster draws upon the latent power of ley lines and telluric currents, utilizing the native forces to empower his spell. On a successful Int check (DC 15+spell level), the caster gains +3 to his spell check without expending any stats. (The caster is then free to spellburn stats to further augment the casting.)","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[2,2],"drawn":false},{"_id":"IxVT55vhkXG4HZDN","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster submits himself to the will of the Fates, who drain the caster of stat points according to their own, unknowable plan. Roll [[/roll 1d4]] to determine the stat drained in the spellburn: (1) Strength, (2) Agility, (3) Stamina, (4) the caster suffers no drain but still receives the spellburn bonus.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[3,3],"drawn":false},{"_id":"n4aXxErKAzMnAswQ","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster cannot spellburn without resorting to a fell chaos rite. His oppressive guilt and the spell’s grim requirements are expressed as Stamina, Strength, or Agility loss. Should the caster ever spellburn in the presence of other agents of the Fates, his life would surely be forfeit.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[4,4],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d4","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true}
{"_id":"KbEH1sdTqyydpaXj","name":"The King of Elfland Spellburn Actions","permission":{"default":0,"wWErSsSXezizF0nw":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"RollTable.iOjHGPxY1RkM00ZX"}},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/elf-helmet.svg","description":"The King of Elfland readily lends his strength to his champions, but few are those that can hold their master’s attention for long. Those that do hope to win their patron’s support must be cunning, clever and courageous. When a caster utilizes spellburn, roll [[/roll 1d4]] and consult the table below or build off the suggestions to create an event specific to your home campaign.","results":[{"_id":"dgNvGRQ5CkdjQjtD","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"A fearsome, scintillating dragon appears over the caster’s shoulder. As the spellburn takes effect, the dragon is drawn into the caster, the shock of the effect manifesting as stat point loss.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[1,1],"drawn":false},{"_id":"fw3CVXlw8LoZCSZZ","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster is granted the spellburn bonus, but must succeed on a minor quest in the next [[/roll 1d4]] weeks; until the quest is completed, the caster cannot regain the burned stat points. The goal of the quest is both trivial and difficult—typically to recover an item with a value only understood by the King of Elfland: a dwarven smith’s favorite anvil; the tiara of a lady-in-waiting; the Black Knight’s shield; the Emperor of the World’s favorite diadem.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[2,2],"drawn":false},{"_id":"1LiFrpUJUMdeO8IB","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Calling on the sylvan realm causes a bit of the caster’s shadow to leave for an errand in the Elflands; forcing one’s own shadow away requires great mental force, manifesting as stat loss.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[3,3],"drawn":false},{"_id":"wauVZpmII3S2sijb","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"In order to succeed on the spellburn, the caster must come up with a pun, riddle or rhyme that delights the King of Elfland. If the King is amused, the PC need not spend any attribute points for the spellburn, but if the King is less  than delighted, the caster must pay twice as many stat points for the burn.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[4,4],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d4","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true}
{"_id":"RE9mEcN8XaWBHGkR","name":"Bobugbubilz Spellburn Actions","permission":{"default":0,"wWErSsSXezizF0nw":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"RollTable.RgG2qH9PP5WIURmE"}},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/frog-prince.svg","description":"Bobugbubilz does not reason like Man, and his requests do not always have an immediate end goal. When a caster utilizes spellburn, roll [[/roll 1d4]] on the table below when a request is made. These ideas should hopefully give you room to expand in your own campaign.","results":[{"_id":"rgEoEsbT8nblVix4","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Bobugbubilz needs the blood of a dry-dweller (a creature that lives only on land). The caster’s blood will do (expressed as Stamina, Strength, or Agility loss).","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[1,1],"drawn":false},{"_id":"kuVyVFy1CRz25FYk","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The demon lord of amphibians needs the feet of a man-creature. In this special situation, the character can spellburn up to 10 points of ability score loss, but need not take any physical action or damage. If he sacrifices the feet of a man-creature (any humanoid will do) to Bobugbubilz before the next sunrise, the character takes no spellburn. If he fails to find such a sacrifice, he takes the full 10 points, distributed across ability scores at the judge’s discretion, at the next sunrise.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[2,2],"drawn":false},{"_id":"AKSibUAewTSD9klh","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Bobugbubilz requires the sweet voice of the caster to make an invocation that his own amphibious servants cannot pronounce properly. Time slows to a crawl as the caster character is whisked away to a dizzying plane of close-quartered, moist, womb-like caverns, where he is forced to read a text written in the words of his native language but with a recondite meaning utterly beyond his comprehension. Upon completing the invocation, he appears back on his native plane. No time seems to have passed, and he finds himself weakened by whatever extent he sacrificed ability score points for spellburn.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[3,3],"drawn":false},{"_id":"N3vOFPNGGDCJJ2mE","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"A slithering host of foul serpents wriggles forth from the ground at the caster’s feet, where they promptly bite his ankles and begin sucking his blood. If the caster resists, the serpents flee and the spellburn fails. If he does not resist, the serpents suck blood until the spellburn is complete as normal, then they wriggle back into the earth. As they disappear below the ground, one turns its head back to offer thanks from Bobugbubilz…then it is gone.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[4,4],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d4","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true}
{"_id":"XWfHFMLTnc10LZVW","name":"Azi Dahaka Spellburn Actions","permission":{"default":0,"wWErSsSXezizF0nw":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"RollTable.3SUBB7Gkgs1LX6jT"}},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/tornado.svg","description":"Azi Dahaka enjoys the wailing cries of his devotees and often encourages even non-followers to call out to him in their times of distress. When a caster  utilizes spellburn, roll [[/roll 1d4]] on the table below or build off the ideas below to create an event specific to your home campaign.","results":[{"_id":"hZ30KnpnAk7psiUr","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"A hot, searing wind centers on the caster, stripping him of bodily fluids, and leaving him parched, blistered and spent (expressed as Stamina, Strength, or Agility loss).","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[1,1],"drawn":false},{"_id":"mPSjbJkvJXM2od64","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The demon prince demands more than the caster can offer. The caster can spellburn up to 10 points of ability score loss but must pay twice that, either in his own ability scores or in HD of creatures slain by the caster. For a sacrifice to qualify, the creature cannot have been summoned, and the caster must strike the killing blow with a ceremonial blade consecrated for the act.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[2,2],"drawn":false},{"_id":"oUODRTX7KiHghXBx","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Azi Dahaka craves a boon of the caster. Within 24 hours of the spellburn, the caster is struck by a burning fever. The caster loses the spellburned attributes while in the grip of the fever and sees a vision of his master’s desire. If the caster successfully undertakes the quest (most often a side trek taking no more than 5 days), he is rewarded as Azi Dahaka sees fit.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[3,3],"drawn":false},{"_id":"xaDpmcFB4Y1VNV00","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The caster crumple to his knees and vomits forth a gout of wet, writhing serpents, leaving him exhausted from the exertion (expressed as Stamina, Strength, or Agility loss). The snakes slither away, vanishing into the ground.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[4,4],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d4","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true}
{"_id":"YanqOfsEBkofHpn6","name":"Sezrekan Spellburn Actions","permission":{"default":0,"wWErSsSXezizF0nw":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"RollTable.Xh1if3a3YDyRtI1j"}},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/evil-eyes.svg","description":"Sezrekan does little to aid his followers. Those that are strong and willful distinguish themselves by their might, while the weak and pitiful are worthless tools to be discarded. And yet, the Old Master has been known to admire those that sacrifice their own bodies in pursuit of the impossible. When a caster utilizes spellburn, roll [[/roll 1d4]] and consult the table below or build off the suggestions to create an event specific to your home campaign.","results":[{"_id":"2R7DkDUjn0Qt7zSZ","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The power of the spellburn opens the caster to the maddening horrors of the universe and leaves him weak (expressed as Stamina, Strength, or Agility loss) and disoriented. The caster must succeed on a DC 15 Will save or be unable to cast spells for [[/roll 1d3]] rounds. If the caster succeeds on the save, the caster gains a +1 bonus to all future attempts at the spell.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[1,1],"drawn":false},{"_id":"DrGTsRl11d1J8vFR","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Admiring the caster’s ambition, Sezrekan grants the caster the opportunity to burn an ally’s attributes (Stamina, Strength or Agility) in place of his own. The target must be willing. For every point burned to augment the spell, the target loses [[/roll 1d3]] points of the same attribute. If any of the target’s attributes fall to 0 or less, the target dies.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[2,2],"drawn":false},{"_id":"i9jLFmCpRFyIVrjv","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Sezrekan mocks the caster’s feeble grasps at power. The caster receives but 1 point for every 2 points of attribute burned.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[3,3],"drawn":false},{"_id":"u4dK2pUTNMBxCAKX","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Horrific madness seizes the caster’s mind, and the awful meaninglessness of the universe is driven deep into his mortal soul. The caster is granted a single DC 15 Will save; on a successful save the caster crumples to his knees, weakened by the spellburn, yet firmly grounded in the common reality. On a failed save—in lieu of the spellburn—the caster receives a +5 bonus to all spell checks for the next [[/roll 1d6]] rounds, yet perceives both friend and foe alike as all-devouring monsters from the outer dark, a truth far too real to contemplate.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[4,4],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d4","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true}
{"_id":"noCBfiD5zGP9yVMw","name":"Table 5-1: Spellburn Actions","permission":{"default":0,"wWErSsSXezizF0nw":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Compendium.dcc-compendiums.dcc-tables.P3jzr9pYVZ1ZiE9i"}},"img":"modules/dcc-core-book/assets/svg/game-icons-net/bleeding-wound.svg","description":"","results":[{"_id":"sltzeygGYzMz7Mh7","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The wizard sacrifices one pound of flesh per spell level, which he must carve from his own body with a knife that is holy to a powerful outsider.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[1,1],"drawn":false},{"_id":"M1C8oEkMUYn3PFnC","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The wizard must spill his own blood – one tablespoon per spell level.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[2,2],"drawn":false},{"_id":"ZDrx3YWiMXeu7Ihb","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The wizard swears an oath to a minor demi-god, who aids him in his time of need but curses him with weakness until the oath is fulfilled.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[3,3],"drawn":false},{"_id":"7onkT2SfboAltpD2","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The wizard cuts off one of his fingertips.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[4,4],"drawn":false},{"_id":"rRtlHGFCQJPI7iv1","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The wizard must yank out his hair and burn it.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[5,5],"drawn":false},{"_id":"x6mNzLLbEZFOLrkm","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The wizard magically enervates his body in order to fuel the spell.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[6,6],"drawn":false},{"_id":"g3coBiK2J7oESREl","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The wizard promises his soul to serve a powerful demon in the afterlife.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[7,7],"drawn":false},{"_id":"LOKBxTdjnspoKqS8","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The wizard agrees to aid followers of a patron saint.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[8,8],"drawn":false},{"_id":"mKcbEKmkt27hmYUb","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The wizard uses a hot iron to brand a supernatural symbol on his arm or torso.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[9,9],"drawn":false},{"_id":"38uXKZeIUdorlI5d","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The wizard must tattoo a mystical symbol on his cheek, forehead, or hand.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[10,10],"drawn":false},{"_id":"imVcXXSdBAnHGfju","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The wizard must pull out a fingernail and burn it with incense.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[11,11],"drawn":false},{"_id":"PuHGucdiSGkd55ve","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The wizard must speak aloud his own true name, weakening himself as a result.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[12,12],"drawn":false},{"_id":"ybtyFkbd0lRWT59S","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The wizard develops a bleeding sore that will not heal until he pays back the aid of the power that assisted him.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[13,13],"drawn":false},{"_id":"vn1bSCEL7R4poKWl","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The wizard must notch his ear in acknowledgment of each time he has been aided.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[14,14],"drawn":false},{"_id":"DNvw7J4dtmih8IQD","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The wizard is required to ritually scarify his back, chest, or biceps with the symbol of a powerful supernatural creature.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[15,15],"drawn":false},{"_id":"eicpO3F7Vt2P29Rz","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The wizard sees maggots drip from his sleeves. When not wearing a shirt, nothing happens and his torso appears normal.  However, when wearing a shirt, he constantly sees maggots falling from his sleeves.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[16,16],"drawn":false},{"_id":"hptZjzvx6pqZbQOu","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The wizard starts to itch! He has strange, uncontrollable itches and scratches constantly.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[17,17],"drawn":false},{"_id":"08geohvTmvPAqt6k","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The wizard develops an odd tic: he twitches his nose, tilts his head, or blinks one eye constantly.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[18,18],"drawn":false},{"_id":"wexsfRUjd1nlKgkU","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The wizard begins muttering under his breath, repeating the name of the entity that has aided him. He can’t stop.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[19,19],"drawn":false},{"_id":"ZiuRgJNvQmCEkEAg","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The wizard must cut his cheeks and let the blood flow down his face.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[20,20],"drawn":false},{"_id":"Fd7eMReyMZ85XXvj","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The wizard must place his hand into an open flame.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[21,21],"drawn":false},{"_id":"DBn6iBhOqNl81GSW","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The wizard must sacrifice one of his most favored possessions.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[22,22],"drawn":false},{"_id":"ViEMtBP63sU1mbyK","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"The wizard must walk on one leg for the remainder of the day.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[23,23],"drawn":false},{"_id":"sSuXyZCjlmcfUSCW","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"Roll again twice.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[24,24],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d24","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true}
